Lingua::SWA::Word2Num — Swahili word to number conversion
Lingua::SWA::Word2Num — Kubadilisha maneno ya nambari ya Kiswahili kuwa tarakimu

Converts Swahili cardinal number text into its numeric value.
Part of the PetaMem Lingua number conversion suite.

SYNOPSIS

    use Lingua::SWA::Word2Num qw(w2n);
    my $num = w2n('...');

    or via the multi-language wrapper:

    use Lingua::Word2Num qw(cardinal);
    my $num = cardinal('sw', '...');

    Both ISO 639-1 ('sw') and ISO 639-3 ('swa') codes are accepted.

INSTALLATION

    shell> cpanm Lingua::SWA::Word2Num

    or install all available languages at once:

    shell> cpanm Task::Lingua::PetaMem

SUPPORTED RANGE

    Integers from 0 to 999,999,999.

SEE ALSO

    Lingua::SWA::Num2Word — the reverse direction
    Lingua::Num2Word      — multi-language number-to-word wrapper
    Lingua::Word2Num      — multi-language word-to-number wrapper
    Task::Lingua::PetaMem — install all languages

